Faculty profile




Stanislaw  JareckiProfessorDEGREE:Ph.D., 2001 Massachusetts Institute of TechnologyRESEARCH AREAS: Algorithms and ComplexityRESEARCH INTERESTS: Professor Jarecki's primary research interest is in applied and distributed cryptography. Specifically, he has made significant contributions to threshold and proactive security and also to digital privacy. Given the current state of the Internet with massively distributed systems of networked computers, all computing is overwhelmingly vulnerable.
CONTACT INFORMATION:

E-mail:
stasio@ics.uci.edu

Office:
DBH 4026

Phone:
(949) 824-8878

Fax:
(949) 824-4056

Website:
